qas.question: Who is Aeneas' enemy throughout the Aeneid?
Which queen committed suicide in Book 4 of the Aeneid?
In which book does Aeneas' father die?
Who reveals Rome's destiny to Aeneas?
Who guides Aeneas through the Underworld?
Who is Jupiter's enemy in the Aeneid?
How many days did Aeneas travel through the underworld?
What did Anchises say Rome's destiny was?

context: Book 1 (at the head of the Odyssean section) opens with a storm which <a0_0>Juno<a0_0/>, Aeneas' enemy throughout the poem, stirs up against the fleet. The storm drives the hero to the coast of Carthage, which historically was Rome's deadliest foe. The queen, <a1_0>Dido<a1_0/>, welcomes the ancestor of the Romans, and under the influence of the gods falls deeply in love with him. At a banquet in Book 2, Aeneas tells the story of the sack of Troy, the death of his wife, and his escape, to the enthralled Carthaginians, while in Book 3 he recounts to them his wanderings over the Mediterranean in search of a suitable new home. Jupiter in Book <b7_0>4<b7_0/> recalls the lingering Aeneas to his duty <b9_0>to found a new city<b9_0/>, and he slips away from <b6_0>Carthage<b6_0/>, leaving <b5_0>Dido<b5_0/> to commit <b8_0>suicide<b8_0/>, cursing Aeneas and calling down revenge in a symbolic anticipation of the fierce wars between Carthage and Rome. In Book <a2_0>5<a2_0/>, Aeneas' father Anchises dies and funeral games are celebrated for him. On reaching Cumae, in Italy in Book 6, Aeneas consults the Cumaean <a4_0>Sibyl<a4_0/>, who conducts him through the Underworld where Aeneas meets the dead <a3_0>Anchises<a3_0/> who reveals Rome's destiny to his son.
